com.openxc.remote.sources
Class AbstractVehicleDataSourceCallback

java.lang.Object
  com.openxc.remote.sources.AbstractVehicleDataSourceCallback
All Implemented Interfaces:
VehicleDataSourceCallbackInterface
public abstract class AbstractVehicleDataSourceCallback
extends Object
implements VehicleDataSourceCallbackInterface

An interface for classes receiving data from a vehicle data source. Vehicle data sources provide updates via a callback for each individual measurement received. Those wishing to receive the updates must register an object extending this class and implemetning the receive(String, Double) and receive(String, Double, Double) methods. Measurements received with String or Boolean values instead of Double are coered to Double by the other receive() methods in this class - those can optionally be overriden if the application has different requirements.

public abstract void receive(String name,
                             Double value,
                             Double event)
Description copied from interface: VehicleDataSourceCallbackInterface
Receive a data point with a name, double value and double event value. This method is similar to VehicleDataSourceCallbackInterface.receive(String, Double) but also accepts the optional event parameter for an OpenXC message. Identical to VehicleDataSourceCallbackInterface.receive(String, Double), the implementation of this method should not block, lest the vehicle data source get behind in processing data from a source potentially external to the system.
